item_list.desc: Power was cut at the Russian-controlled Chernobyl nuclear plant and there’s a risk of “nuclear discharge,” according to Ukrainian officials. #ukraine

stickerText:
⚠️ There’s a risk of
a radioactive leak at Chernobyl nuclear plant, Ukraine has warned. ⚠️

Power was cut at
the plant on Mar. 9th, and Ukrainian officials are blaming Russia.
Russian forces took control of Chernobyl on Feb. 24th
and, according to Ukrainian officials, have since refused to let staff members leave.

By Mar. 8th, the remote data transmission from safeguards monitoring systems had also
been lost, per the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).

Ukrainian officials say without electricity,
the pumps cannot cool and evaporation will occur, leading to “nuclear discharge.”

Energoatom,
Ukraine’s state-run nuclear company, posted a warning message on Mar. 9th on the instant-messaging app Telegram.
The IAEA was informed and sees “no critical impact on safety.”
